00:44:08.390 --> 00:44:09.710
to say you identify as.

00:44:09.710 --> 00:44:11.430
So yeah, we get that a lot.

00:44:11.430 --> 00:44:14.360
And I guess there's a
lot to unpack there.

00:44:14.360 --> 00:44:17.250
I'm bisexual, so I've had a
lot of, that's just a phase.

00:44:17.250 --> 00:44:18.350
I've had a lot of that.

00:44:18.350 --> 00:44:21.120
Now, I came out at nine.

00:44:21.120 --> 00:44:22.250
I am now 28.

00:44:22.250 --> 00:44:23.810
It is a long phase.

00:44:23.810 --> 00:44:26.560
But so what if it was?

00:44:26.560 --> 00:44:28.490
Ultimately, so what?

00:44:28.490 --> 00:44:30.590
Should we be such
gatekeepers, or should we

00:44:30.590 --> 00:44:31.799
leave that door open?

00:44:31.799 --> 00:44:34.340
And should we allow people to
explore their gender identities

00:44:34.340 --> 00:44:36.800
and their sexuality and their
sexual orientation and all

00:44:36.800 --> 00:44:38.811
these-- and their gender
expression, as well?

00:44:38.811 --> 00:44:41.060
I think we should be far
more fluid about these things

00:44:41.060 --> 00:44:44.300
because that allows
people to not

00:44:44.300 --> 00:44:47.840
have to be so sure before
they say anything about it.

00:44:47.840 --> 00:44:50.202
And that pent-up
anxiety is where

00:44:50.202 --> 00:44:52.160
we have what's called
minority stress, the fact

00:44:52.160 --> 00:44:55.460
that you're in a minority group
being a stressful experience

00:44:55.460 --> 00:44:58.890
even before you experience
any sort of discrimination.

00:44:58.890 --> 00:45:03.990
So I just think the answer to
this is to not care as much.

00:45:03.990 --> 00:45:07.790
But that doesn't mean you
get away with not knowing

00:45:07.790 --> 00:45:08.840
how to be respectful.

00:45:08.840 --> 00:45:10.310
Those two things
aren't the same.

00:45:10.310 --> 00:45:12.830
Just saying I don't care
how people identify,

00:45:12.830 --> 00:45:14.720
that's not helpful.

00:45:14.720 --> 00:45:18.380
We should all care about what
makes someone comfortable

00:45:18.380 --> 00:45:21.050
and what makes someone's
movement through this world

00:45:21.050 --> 00:45:23.270
easier, especially when
what we're asked to do

00:45:23.270 --> 00:45:25.500
is so easy on our behalf.

00:45:25.500 --> 00:45:27.800
Ask people's
pronouns, not assume

00:45:27.800 --> 00:45:31.640
if they're straight or gay or bi
or whatever, not slagging them

00:45:31.640 --> 00:45:32.450
for what they wear.

00:45:32.450 --> 00:45:34.250
These are really
simple things to do.

00:45:34.250 --> 00:45:36.950
It's like the way
buildings are accessible.

00:45:36.950 --> 00:45:39.514
That's an easy way to make
some people's life-- are they

00:45:39.514 --> 00:45:40.180
in the minority?

00:45:40.180 --> 00:45:40.670
Yeah.

00:45:40.670 --> 00:45:41.750
Does that mean we
shouldn't care about them?

00:45:41.750 --> 00:45:42.620
No.

00:45:42.620 --> 00:45:46.730
So I don't think there's any
limits to self-identification.

00:45:46.730 --> 00:45:48.530
The question is, what
does that mean you're

00:45:48.530 --> 00:45:49.940
asking other people to do?

00:45:49.940 --> 00:45:51.689
If you're saying, I
identify as nonbinary,

00:45:51.689 --> 00:45:53.990
or genderfluid, what are you
asking other people to do?

00:45:53.990 --> 00:45:57.207
You're asking them to
use maybe a name that

00:45:57.207 --> 00:45:58.790
isn't on their birth
cert and pronouns

00:45:58.790 --> 00:46:00.140
that you might
have not heard of,

00:46:00.140 --> 00:46:02.348
like "they" and "them" or
"ze" and "zem" or something

00:46:02.348 --> 00:46:03.110
like that.

00:46:03.110 --> 00:46:05.930
If you identify as
an attack helicopter,

00:46:05.930 --> 00:46:08.570
what are you asking
people to do?

00:46:08.570 --> 00:46:11.840
Are you asking them to
have a helicopter landing

00:46:11.840 --> 00:46:14.630
pad for their work?

00:46:14.630 --> 00:46:15.320
Maybe you are.

00:46:15.320 --> 00:46:16.160
I don't know.

00:46:16.160 --> 00:46:18.860
But if it's something I can
do, I'll actually do it.

00:46:18.860 --> 00:46:20.552
I don't care if that's
how you identify.

00:46:20.552 --> 00:46:22.760
But you're just being
facetious when people say that.

00:46:22.760 --> 00:46:23.760
Of course they are.

00:46:23.760 --> 00:46:28.480
But the way to counteract
that obvious, ridiculous claim

00:46:28.480 --> 00:46:30.530
